content.text:
Now I have a thorough understanding of all the patterns. Here is the complete implementation plan.

---

## Bus Tab Implementation Plan

### Architecture Overview

The feature follows the exact same three-layer pattern used by `ClassScheduleScreen`:

```
SavedBusTrip (data model)
    ↓
BusRepository (Gson + SharedPreferences, singleton, MutableStateFlow, seeded defaults)
    ↓
BusScheduleViewModel (thin delegate, ViewModelProvider.Factory with Context, StateFlow)
    ↓
BusScheduleScreen (LocalContext → viewModel, collectAsState, Scaffold + FAB + dialogs)
```

There is one additional concern not present in the Class screen: time-aware logic (parsing "8:30 AM" strings into `LocalTime` for sorting and countdown). This logic lives entirely in the ViewModel/Screen layer — the repository stores raw strings.

---

## Step 1 — `data/SavedBusTrip.kt`

Create the data model exactly as proposed. No changes needed from the spec.

```kotlin
package com.example.combined_schedule.data

import java.util.UUID

data class SavedBusTrip(
    val id: String = UUID.randomUUID().toString(),
    val routeName: String,
    val stopName: String,
    val direction: String = "",
    val departureTimes: List<String> = emptyList(),  // e.g. ["8:30 AM", "10:30 AM"]
    val daysOfWeek: List<String> = listOf("Mon","Tue","Wed","Thu","Fri"),
    val isFavorite: Boolean = false,
    val notes: String = ""
)
```

Key decisions:
- `departureTimes` is `List<String>` rather than `List<LocalTime>` to keep it serializable via Gson without a custom type adapter — consistent with how `ScheduleEntry` stores `time: String`.
- `daysOfWeek` uses the same short strings ("Mon","Tue",...) that the filter chips will display, avoiding a separate mapping layer.
- No `@SerializedName` annotations needed since field names are used as JSON keys and Gson handles data classes directly (same as `Work` and `ScheduleEntry`).

---

## Step 2 — `data/BusRepository.kt`

Mirror `ScheduleEntryRepository` precisely.

```kotlin
package com.example.combined_schedule.data

import android.content.Context
import com.google.gson.Gson
import com.google.gson.reflect.TypeToken
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.MutableStateFlow
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.StateFlow
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.asStateFlow

class BusRepository(context: Context) {

    private val prefs    = context.getSharedPreferences("bus_trips_prefs", Context.MODE_PRIVATE)
    private val gson     = Gson()
    private val listType = object : TypeToken<List<SavedBusTrip>>() {}.type

    private val _trips = MutableStateFlow<List<SavedBusTrip>>(loadAll())

    init { if (!prefs.getBoolean(KEY_SEEDED, false)) seedDefaults() }

    fun getAll(): StateFlow<List<SavedBusTrip>> = _trips.asStateFlow()

    private fun loadAll(): List<SavedBusTrip> {
        val json = prefs.getString(KEY, null) ?: return emptyList()
        return gson.fromJson(json, listType) ?: emptyList()
    }

    private fun saveAll(trips: List<SavedBusTrip>) {
        prefs.edit().putString(KEY, gson.toJson(trips)).apply()
        _trips.value = trips
    }

    fun insert(trip: SavedBusTrip) = saveAll(_trips.value + trip)
    fun update(trip: SavedBusTrip) = saveAll(_trips.value.map { if (it.id == trip.id) trip else it })
    fun delete(trip: SavedBusTrip) = saveAll(_trips.value.filter { it.id != trip.id })

    private fun seedDefaults() {
        val defaults = listOf(
            SavedBusTrip(
                routeName      = "22 Illini",
                stopName       = "Green & Wright",
                direction      = "Northbound",
                departureTimes = listOf("8:30 AM", "10:30 AM", "2:00 PM", "4:30 PM")
            ),
            SavedBusTrip(
                routeName      = "Silver (CUMTD 5)",
                stopName       = "Orchard Downs",
                direction      = "Loop",
                departureTimes = listOf("7:45 AM", "12:15 PM", "5:00 PM")
            ),
            SavedBusTrip(
                routeName      = "Green (CUMTD 12)",
                stopName       = "Main & Wright",
                direction      = "Eastbound",
                departureTimes = listOf("9:00 AM", "1:00 PM", "3:30 PM")
            )
        )
        saveAll(defaults)
        prefs.edit().putBoolean(KEY_SEEDED, true).apply()
    }

    companion object {
        private const val KEY        = "all_bus_trips"
        private const val KEY_SEEDED = "bus_seeded_defaults"

        @Volatile private var INSTANCE: BusRepository? = null

        fun getInstance(context: Context): BusRepository =
            INSTANCE ?: synchronized(this) {
                BusRepository(context.applicationContext).also { INSTANCE = it }
            }
    }
}
```

Notes:
- SharedPreferences key `"bus_trips_prefs"` is distinct from `"schedule_entries_prefs"` and `"works_prefs"`.
- `saveAll` is the single mutation point — it writes to disk and updates the flow atomically, matching the existing pattern exactly.
- The seeded Silver route uses `daysOfWeek = listOf("Mon","Tue","Wed","Thu","Fri")` (the default) so no override is needed for that field in the seed.

---

## Step 3 — `ui/viewmodel/BusScheduleViewModel.kt`

```kotlin
package com.example.combined_schedule.ui.viewmodel

import android.content.Context
import androidx.lifecycle.ViewModel
import androidx.lifecycle.ViewModelProvider
import com.example.combined_schedule.data.BusRepository
import com.example.combined_schedule.data.SavedBusTrip
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.StateFlow

class BusScheduleViewModel(private val repo: BusRepository) : ViewModel() {

    val trips: StateFlow<List<SavedBusTrip>> = repo.getAll()

    fun insert(trip: SavedBusTrip) = repo.insert(trip)
    fun update(trip: SavedBusTrip) = repo.update(trip)
    fun delete(trip: SavedBusTrip) = repo.delete(trip)

    class Factory(private val context: Context) : ViewModelProvider.Factory {
        @Suppress("UNCHECKED_CAST")
        override fun <T : ViewModel> create(modelClass: Class<T>): T =
            BusScheduleViewModel(BusRepository.getInstance(context)) as T
    }
}
```

This is deliberately thin — identical shape to `ClassScheduleViewModel`. All display-side derived state (filtering by day, parsing times for sorting, computing countdown) is computed in the Screen with `remember(...)` blocks, which is exactly how `ClassScheduleScreen` handles its `displayed` list and `dateEntryMap`.

---

## Step 4 — `ui/screens/BusScheduleScreen.kt` (full rewrite)

### 4a. File-level constants and helpers

```kotlin
// ── Bus color palette ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
private val busAccent     = Color(0xFFE65100)   // deep orange — MTD brand-adjacent
private val busContainer  = Color(0xFFFFF3E0)   // orange 50
private val busFavorite   = Color(0xFFFFB300)   // amber for star

private val ALL_DAYS = listOf("Sun","Mon","Tue","Wed","Thu","Fri","Sat")

/** Parse "h:mm AM/PM" → LocalTime, null on failure. */
private fun parseTime(s: String): LocalTime? = try {
    LocalTime.parse(s.trim(), DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("h:mm a"))
} catch (_: Exception) { null }

/** Today's short day name, e.g. "Mon". */
private fun todayShortDay(): String =
    LocalDate.now().dayOfWeek
        .getDisplayName(java.time.format.TextStyle.SHORT, java.util.Locale.ENGLISH)
        .replaceFirstChar { it.uppercase() }   // "Mon", "Tue", …
```

### 4b. Screen entry point signature

```kotlin
@Composable
fun BusScheduleScreen()
```

No parameters needed — navigation is not required inside the screen (no deep-link destinations launched from here).

### 4c. State declarations inside `BusScheduleScreen`

```kotlin
val context       = LocalContext.current
val vm: BusScheduleViewModel = viewModel(factory = BusScheduleViewModel.Factory(context))
val allTrips by vm.trips.collectAsState()

// live clock, refreshed every 30 s (same pattern as HomeScreen)
var currentTime by remember { mutableStateOf(LocalTime.now()) }
LaunchedEffect(Unit) { while (true) { delay(30_000L); currentTime = LocalTime.now() } }

// selected day defaults to today; clicking again deselects (same as ClassScheduleScreen date toggle)
var selectedDay  by remember { mutableStateOf(todayShortDay()) }

var showDialog   by remember { mutableStateOf(false) }
var editingTrip  by remember { mutableStateOf<SavedBusTrip?>(null) }

// Trips active on selectedDay, sorted by soonest departure time for that day
val filteredTrips = remember(allTrips, selectedDay) {
    allTrips
        .filter { selectedDay in it.daysOfWeek }
        .sortedBy { trip ->
            trip.departureTimes
                .mapNotNull { parseTime(it) }
                .minOrNull()
                ?: LocalTime.MAX
        }
}

// Next bus: the trip+time closest in the future among today's active trips
val nextBusInfo: Pair<SavedBusTrip, LocalTime>? = remember(allTrips, currentTime) {
    val today = todayShortDay()
    allTrips
        .filter { today in it.daysOfWeek }
        .flatMap { trip -> trip.departureTimes.mapNotNull { t -> parseTime(t)?.let { trip to it } } }
        .filter { (_, t) -> !t.isBefore(currentTime) }
        .minByOrNull { (_, t) -> t }
}
```

### 4d. Scaffold + FAB structure

```kotlin
Scaffold(
    floatingActionButton = {
        FloatingActionButton(
            onClick = { editingTrip = null; showDialog = true },
            containerColor = busAccent
        ) { Icon(Icons.Default.Add, "Add bus route") }
    }
) { innerPadding ->
    LazyColumn(
        modifier = Modifier.fillMaxSize().padding(innerPadding),
        contentPadding = PaddingValues(bottom = 80.dp)
    ) {
        // (1) Next Bus Banner
        item { NextBusBanner(info = nextBusInfo, currentTime = currentTime) }

        // (2) Day-of-week filter chips
        item { DayFilterRow(selectedDay = selectedDay, onDaySelected = { selectedDay = it }) }

        // (3) Empty state OR route cards
        if (filteredTrips.isEmpty()) {
            item { BusEmptyState() }
        } else {
            items(filteredTrips, key = { it.id }) { trip ->
                Box(modifier = Modifier.padding(horizontal = 16.dp, vertical = 5.dp)) {
                    BusTripCard(
                        trip        = trip,
                        currentTime = currentTime,
                        selectedDay = selectedDay,
                        onEdit      = { editingTrip = trip; showDialog = true },
                        onDelete    = { vm.delete(trip) },
                        onFavorite  = { vm.update(trip.copy(isFavorite = !trip.isFavorite)) }
                    )
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

if (showDialog) {
    BusTripDialog(
        initial   = editingTrip,
        onDismiss = { showDialog = false },
        onConfirm = { trip ->
            if (editingTrip == null) vm.insert(trip) else vm.update(trip)
            showDialog = false
        }
    )
}
```

### 4e. `NextBusBanner` composable

```kotlin
@Composable
private fun NextBusBanner(
    info: Pair<SavedBusTrip, LocalTime>?,
    currentTime: LocalTime
)
```

- Mirrors `HomeScreen`'s `NextEventBanner` shape (card with `primaryContainer` background, "UP NEXT BUS" label, countdown chip).
- Countdown logic: `Duration.between(currentTime, departureTime).toMinutes()` — identical computation to `NextEventBanner`.
- Displays: route name + direction as title, stop name as subtitle, departure time formatted with `DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("h:mm a")`.
- When `info == null`: renders a small muted card "No more buses today" using `surfaceVariant` — mirrors `NoMoreEventsCard`.
- The countdown chip uses `busAccent` as its background (instead of `primary`) to maintain the orange bus theme.

### 4f. `DayFilterRow` composable

```kotlin
@Composable
private fun DayFilterRow(
    selectedDay: String,
    onDaySelected: (String) -> Unit
)
```

- `LazyRow` with `horizontalArrangement = Arrangement.spacedBy(8.dp)` and `contentPadding = PaddingValues(horizontal = 16.dp)` — same as the filter chip row in `ClassScheduleScreen`.
- Iterates `ALL_DAYS` ("Sun" through "Sat"). Today's day gets a subtle suffix asterisk or distinct `FilterChipDefaults.filterChipColors` with `selectedContainerColor = busAccent` and `selectedLabelColor = Color.White` — same approach as `EntryDialog`'s type chips.
- Tapping the already-selected day does nothing (stays selected — a day filter must always have a value, unlike the entry type filter which can be null/"All").

### 4g. `BusTripCard` composable

```kotlin
@Composable
private fun BusTripCard(
    trip: SavedBusTrip,
    currentTime: LocalTime,
    selectedDay: String,
    onEdit: () -> Unit,
    onDelete: () -> Unit,
    onFavorite: () -> Unit
)
```

Internal structure (mirrors `ScheduleEntryCard`):

```
Card (busContainer background, clickable → onEdit)
  Row (IntrinsicSize.Min height)
    Box (5.dp wide, busAccent left accent bar, same pattern as ScheduleEntryCard)
    Column (weight 1f, 12dp horizontal / 10dp vertical padding)
      Row                         ← header row
        Surface (busAccent badge) ← "BUS" label chip (same shape as entryLabel chip)
        Text(routeName + direction)  ← title in busAccent color, FontWeight.SemiBold
      Text(stopName)              ← subtitle in onSurfaceVariant
      Spacer(4.dp)
      TimeChipsRow(               ← departure times for selectedDay
          times = trip.departureTimes,
          currentTime = currentTime
      )
      if (notes.isNotBlank()) Text(notes, labelSmall, onSurfaceVariant)
    Column (right side actions, aligned CenterVertically)
      IconButton (Star, tint = if favorite busFavorite else onSurfaceVariant 35%)
      IconButton (Delete, tint = busAccent 40%)
```

The `TimeChipsRow` sub-composable:

```kotlin
@Composable
private fun TimeChipsRow(times: List<String>, currentTime: LocalTime)
```

- Renders each time as a small `Surface(RoundedCornerShape(12.dp))`.
- The soonest upcoming time (first time where `parseTime(t)?.isAfter(currentTime) == true`) gets `busAccent` background with white text.
- Past times get `onSurface.copy(alpha = 0.25f)` (greyed out).
- Future-but-not-soonest times get `busContainer` with `busAccent` text.
- Uses a `FlowRow` pattern: since this is a horizontal sequence that might wrap, use a `LazyRow` with `Arrangement.spacedBy(4.dp)` — or, since the count is small (max ~6 items), a simple `Row` wrapping in a `FlowRow`-style by iterating in pairs would work. The simplest correct approach is a regular non-lazy `Row` with `horizontalArrangement = Arrangement.spacedBy(4.dp)` and `modifier = Modifier.horizontalScroll(rememberScrollState())` to handle overflow without requiring an external library.

### 4h. `BusEmptyState` composable

```kotlin
@Composable
private fun BusEmptyState()
```

- Centered `Box` with `padding(vertical = 60.dp)`.
- Bus icon emoji + "No saved routes for [selectedDay]" text.
- Muted instruction: "Tap + to save a UIUC MTD route."
- Uses `MaterialTheme.typography.bodyMedium` + `onSurfaceVariant` color — same empty state pattern as `ClassScheduleScreen`.

### 4i. `BusTripDialog` composable

```kotlin
@Composable
private fun BusTripDialog(
    initial: SavedBusTrip?,
    onDismiss: () -> Unit,
    onConfirm: (SavedBusTrip) -> Unit
)
```

Internal state variables:

```kotlin
var routeName    by remember { mutableStateOf(initial?.routeName    ?: "") }
var stopName     by remember { mutableStateOf(initial?.stopName     ?: "") }
var direction    by remember { mutableStateOf(initial?.direction    ?: "") }
var timesText    by remember { mutableStateOf(initial?.departureTimes?.joinToString(", ") ?: "") }
var selectedDays by remember { mutableStateOf(initial?.daysOfWeek   ?: listOf("Mon","Tue","Wed","Thu","Fri")) }
var notes        by remember { mutableStateOf(initial?.notes        ?: "") }
```

`AlertDialog` layout (inside `text = { Column(...) }`):

1. `OutlinedTextField` — "Route Name *" (singleLine = true, required for `confirmButton` enabled)
2. `OutlinedTextField` — "Stop Name *" (singleLine = true, required)
3. `OutlinedTextField` — "Direction" (singleLine = true, placeholder "Northbound")
4. `OutlinedTextField` — "Departure Times" (placeholder "8:30 AM, 10:30 AM, 2:00 PM", singleLine = false, maxLines = 2). Times are parsed from comma-separated input on confirm.
5. Day-of-week multi-select using `LazyRow` of `FilterChip` — iterate `ALL_DAYS`, `selected = day in selectedDays`, toggle on click: `selectedDays = if (day in selectedDays) selectedDays - day else selectedDays + day`. Uses same `FilterChipDefaults.filterChipColors(selectedContainerColor = busAccent, selectedLabelColor = Color.White)` as type chips in `EntryDialog`.
6. `OutlinedTextField` — "Notes" (maxLines = 2, optional).

`confirmButton`:
```kotlin
TextButton(
    onClick = {
        val parsedTimes = timesText.split(",")
            .map { it.trim() }
            .filter { it.isNotBlank() }
        onConfirm(SavedBusTrip(
            id             = initial?.id ?: UUID.randomUUID().toString(),
            routeName      = routeName.trim(),
            stopName       = stopName.trim(),
            direction      = direction.trim(),
            departureTimes = parsedTimes,
            daysOfWeek     = selectedDays,
            isFavorite     = initial?.isFavorite ?: false,
            notes          = notes.trim()
        ))
    },
    enabled = routeName.isNotBlank() && stopName.isNotBlank()
) { Text(if (initial == null) "Add" else "Save") }
```

---

## Step 5 — No changes needed to `MainActivity.kt`

The route `Screen.Bus` already maps to `BusScheduleScreen()` at line 113. Since the rewritten screen keeps the same no-parameter composable signature `fun BusScheduleScreen()`, the navigation wiring requires zero changes.

---

## Step 6 — Time Parsing Strategy and Edge Cases

The most non-trivial logic is `parseTime()`. The format "8:30 AM" needs `DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("h:mm a")`. Two gotchas:

1. `LocalTime.parse()` is locale-sensitive for the AM/PM marker. Use `Locale.ENGLISH` explicitly:
   ```kotlin
   private fun parseTime(s: String): LocalTime? = try {
       LocalTime.parse(
           s.trim().uppercase(java.util.Locale.ENGLISH),
           DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("h:mm a", java.util.Locale.ENGLISH)
       )
   } catch (_: Exception) { null }
   ```
2. Times stored as "12:15 PM" and "5:00 PM" both parse correctly with `h:mm a`. "7:45 AM" also fine. No edge case with 12-hour format.

The countdown minutes calculation in `NextBusBanner`:

```kotlin
val minutesUntil = Duration.between(currentTime, departureTime).toMinutes()
val countdownText = when {
    minutesUntil <= 0  -> "Now"
    minutesUntil < 60  -> "in $minutesUntil min"
    else -> { val h = minutesUntil/60; val m = minutesUntil%60
              if (m == 0L) "in ${h}h" else "in ${h}h ${m}m" }
}
```

This is an exact copy of the logic in `HomeScreen`'s `NextEventBanner`.

